citations:
    citation-acok-theon-i:
        source: source-acok
        properties:
            locator: "Theon I"
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Theon Greyjoy, arriving at Lordsport on the Myraham. Greeted at Lordsport by his uncle Aeron Greyjoy (Damphair), now a priest of the Drowned God. Theon rides to Pyke and meets Lord Balon Greyjoy. Balon rejects Robb Stark's offer of alliance, burns the letter, and reveals he intends to take the North himself. Names of Theon's dead brothers Rodrik (slain by Lord Jason Mallister at Seagard) and Maron (crushed in the collapse of the south tower of Pyke during the Greyjoy Rebellion) confirmed."
